1
00:00:02,045 --> 00:00:05,066
It's a grimoire written by
Flamme, the legendary mage?

2
00:00:05,927 --> 00:00:09,128
No, books supposedly attributed
to Flamme are never real.

3
00:00:09,988 --> 00:00:12,629
Every tome uncovered so
far has been a fabrication.

4
00:00:14,030 --> 00:00:17,611
This is probably the best imitation
I've come across over the years, though.

5
00:00:18,272 --> 00:00:21,233
It's not a terrible reward to
receive for defeating monsters.

6
00:00:21,647 --> 00:00:22,407
If you say so.

7
00:00:22,948 --> 00:00:23,888
I don't see the appeal.

8
00:00:24,568 --> 00:00:25,229
What a shame.

9
00:00:25,669 --> 00:00:31,071
When you find nothing but forgeries, you start to doubt
whether the genuine article ever existed in the first place.

10
00:00:31,691 --> 00:00:34,893
The Great Flamme,
founder of humanity's magic.

11
00:00:35,573 --> 00:00:37,794
To be fair, it's
like a fairy tale.

12
00:00:38,274 --> 00:00:39,595
Is that what people believe?

13
00:00:41,676 --> 00:00:45,277
I suppose enough years have passed
that she's become something of a myth.

14
00:00:47,038 --> 00:00:51,360
I might be the only one left alive who
knew her, who remembers her face.

15
00:01:01,355 --> 00:01:01,955
Good morning.

16
00:01:07,296 --> 00:01:08,137
It's a miracle!

17
00:01:08,157 --> 00:01:09,297
She woke up early!

18
00:01:09,797 --> 00:01:11,818
Okay, and you're
shocked by that?

19
00:01:12,118 --> 00:01:12,778
Astounded.

20
00:01:14,858 --> 00:01:16,959
This is deserving of a reward.

21
00:01:24,300 --> 00:01:25,700
What is happening?

22
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:13,041
My most humble thanks.

23
00:03:13,401 --> 00:03:17,563
When I saw this landslide, I feared I
would never find a way through the pass.

24
00:03:24,647 --> 00:03:27,968
Hey, uh, is this
actually necessary?

25
00:03:28,188 --> 00:03:29,109
Are you unhappy?

26
00:03:29,629 --> 00:03:30,990
He's offered a fine reward.

27
00:03:31,010 --> 00:03:32,871
No, that's not the issue.

28
00:03:32,891 --> 00:03:36,072
This would go faster if you just
used your magic to move his cart.

29
00:03:36,913 --> 00:03:38,414
But what of future travelers?

30
00:03:38,574 --> 00:03:39,454
They'd be stuck here.

31
00:03:40,114 --> 00:03:41,015
That's what Fern said.

32
00:03:43,206 --> 00:03:45,388
We wouldn't want to be
selfish now, would we?

33
00:03:46,408 --> 00:03:47,689
That's rich coming from you.

34
00:03:51,592 --> 00:03:52,913
I insist you have a drink.

35
00:03:53,274 --> 00:03:53,974
Oh, thanks.

36
00:03:54,394 --> 00:03:55,015
That'd be great.

37
00:04:01,947 --> 00:04:02,587
It's strange.

38
00:04:03,828 --> 00:04:05,889
I thought landslides
happened on a bigger scale.

39
00:04:06,510 --> 00:04:12,673
The Northern Lands have been fighting demons in this area, and
their clashes have had a far-reaching impact on local terrain.

40
00:04:13,034 --> 00:04:15,315
This was likely caused
by such a skirmish.

41
00:04:16,456 --> 00:04:18,657
So now we're tending
to the scars of battle.

42
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:26,662
Mr. Stark, would you
mind helping me over here?

43
00:04:27,122 --> 00:04:28,983
I could use your
assistance for a moment.

44
00:04:31,815 --> 00:04:32,675
Mr. Stark?

45
00:04:34,016 --> 00:04:36,696
Hey, could you maybe
drop the Mr. part?

46
00:04:36,956 --> 00:04:37,717
Stark is fine.

47
00:04:39,237 --> 00:04:40,197
It weirds me out.

48
00:04:40,657 --> 00:04:42,558
I'm pretty sure we're
close to the same age.

49
00:04:45,059 --> 00:04:45,759
Very well.

50
00:04:46,819 --> 00:04:47,699
If you'd prefer it.

51
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:51,620
Stark, you're wasting
everyone's time.

52
00:04:51,761 --> 00:04:52,181
Help me.

53
00:04:52,401 --> 00:04:53,141
Dude!

54
00:04:53,681 --> 00:04:57,662
I just meant that if we're gonna go on this
journey together, you can drop the formalities.

55
00:04:57,682 --> 00:05:00,283
We can talk to
each other casually.

56
00:05:01,725 --> 00:05:04,005
And it wouldn't hurt you to
be a little friendlier, you know.

57
00:05:04,025 --> 00:05:06,246
I'm a warrior with
a sensitive soul.

58
00:05:06,806 --> 00:05:08,026
What a pain in the rear.

59
00:05:08,126 --> 00:05:09,166
What'd you call me?!

60
00:05:10,047 --> 00:05:11,787
I assume you're
making good progress?

61
00:05:12,667 --> 00:05:13,387
You heard her.

62
00:05:13,647 --> 00:05:15,528
Let's hurry, Mr. Stark.

63
00:05:16,408 --> 00:05:16,948
Fine.

64
00:05:18,908 --> 00:05:21,829
Ah, you have my
undying gratitude.

65
00:05:22,109 --> 00:05:25,049
If you'd like, I can show you
the fastest route into town.

66
00:05:26,270 --> 00:05:28,450
I have the honor of
escorting an elf, eh?

67
00:05:29,235 --> 00:05:33,418
I've lived for many decades, but this is
my first time meeting one of your kind.

68
00:05:33,798 --> 00:05:35,540
I suppose we are a rarity.

69
00:05:37,081 --> 00:05:40,803
Now that I'm thinking about it, you're
the only one I've ever seen in person, too.

70
00:05:41,224 --> 00:05:42,585
There aren't very many of us.

71
00:05:44,186 --> 00:05:47,468
In fact, I've only ever met a handful
of other elves in all my travels.

72
00:05:48,569 --> 00:05:51,431
We may live a long time, but
we've scattered to the winds.

73
00:05:52,192 --> 00:05:56,555
Of course, it doesn't help that we don't have
romantic urges or reproductive instincts.

74
00:05:57,634 --> 00:05:59,836
We're experiencing
a quiet extinction.

75
00:06:00,516 --> 00:06:03,979
Over 400 years have gone by
since I've laid eyes on another elf.

76
00:06:05,140 --> 00:06:06,781
We may be close to disappearing.

77
00:06:16,409 --> 00:06:18,070
This is a lovely
view of the town.

78
00:06:19,711 --> 00:06:21,292
It's a busy day at the gate.

79
00:06:22,053 --> 00:06:23,594
Those look like merchant wagons.

80
00:06:23,614 --> 00:06:25,656
The Liberation
Festival is tonight.

81
00:06:27,409 --> 00:06:35,193
It was on this very day, many moons ago, that Himmel and his
party of heroes defeated the demons who plagued this land.

82
00:06:36,393 --> 00:06:38,674
That must have been quite
the experience for them.

83
00:06:39,835 --> 00:06:42,856
The Liberation Festival
commemorates their triumph.

84
00:06:43,797 --> 00:06:51,500
Every year, the statues of Mr. Himmel and his companions in the Central
Plaza are decorated, and the town throws a grand celebration around them.

85
00:06:52,461 --> 00:06:54,002
Humans love to make a fuss.

86
00:06:54,742 --> 00:06:56,783
They'll use any
excuse to hold a festival.

87
00:06:57,427 --> 00:07:02,170
More than 80 years have passed since the demons
were finally defeated on that auspicious day.

88
00:07:03,311 --> 00:07:08,295
That's plenty of time for even something so
important to begin fading from the minds of men.

89
00:07:09,516 --> 00:07:11,217
But we can't have that.

90
00:07:12,518 --> 00:07:17,021
And so we celebrate in remembrance
of those who fought on our behalf.

91
00:07:21,964 --> 00:07:22,625
Excellent work.

92
00:07:24,522 --> 00:07:26,163
The fifth time's a charm.

93
00:07:26,584 --> 00:07:28,745
This sculptor worked
faster than previous ones.

94
00:07:29,526 --> 00:07:32,729
You are constantly getting statues
put up in your honor, Himmel.

95
00:07:33,669 --> 00:07:36,372
Well, how else can I assure
that people will remember us?

96
00:07:37,653 --> 00:07:39,554
Our lives are fleeting
compared to yours.

97
00:07:39,574 --> 00:07:41,255
We won't be around for long.

98
00:07:42,797 --> 00:07:44,078
Take a look at this face!

99
00:07:44,318 --> 00:07:46,660
Future generations must
see how handsome I was!

100
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:48,261
Whatever, I'm
heading back to the inn.

101
00:07:50,003 --> 00:07:52,845
Though... there is
a greater reason.

102
00:07:53,921 --> 00:07:58,144
When we three are gone, maybe our
statues will keep you from feeling lonely.

103
00:08:00,445 --> 00:08:00,946
Come again?

104
00:08:02,627 --> 00:08:03,908
You'll know we existed.

105
00:08:04,828 --> 00:08:08,290
That we aren't just fairy tales,
but people who stood beside you.

106
00:08:13,854 --> 00:08:19,498
Every year, we gather in celebration of the spectacular
deeds accomplished by this brave band of heroes.

107
00:08:21,461 --> 00:08:27,803
Now that we're here, I must say that you bear a striking
resemblance to Miss Frieren, that mighty mage of yore.

108
00:08:30,264 --> 00:08:32,825
Will they still be doing this
a hundred years from now?

109
00:08:33,485 --> 00:08:36,446
Oh yes, for as long
as this town stands.

110
00:08:37,026 --> 00:08:37,866
A thousand years?

111
00:08:39,907 --> 00:08:42,107
That's more
difficult to foresee.

112
00:08:48,990 --> 00:08:50,370
Well, shall we be off?

113
00:08:51,762 --> 00:08:53,143
We have a long road ahead of us.

114
00:08:54,885 --> 00:08:58,849
Speaking of which, you haven't told
me what our final destination is yet.

115
00:08:58,869 --> 00:09:00,271
Where are we going?

116
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:05,004
To heaven.

117
00:09:06,237 --> 00:09:07,018
That sounds fun.

118
00:09:25,103 --> 00:09:26,424
There are a lot of guards here.

119
00:09:27,485 --> 00:09:28,865
Do you suppose
something happened?

120
00:09:30,226 --> 00:09:32,548
Maybe we should decide who'll
be in charge of the shopping.

121
00:09:40,673 --> 00:09:42,494
We're in town, Mistress Frieren.

122
00:09:43,054 --> 00:09:43,815
Demons approach.

123
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:09,382
Well, Graf Granat, did
you hire an elf to kill us?

124
00:10:10,523 --> 00:10:11,523
I can't take credit.

125
00:10:12,304 --> 00:10:15,545
Though it's true I despise you and
pray for your death, Lord Lugner.

126
00:10:16,506 --> 00:10:20,208
I wouldn't be so bold as to openly
attack a peace envoy in the center of town.

127
00:10:21,048 --> 00:10:21,749
I'm no fool.

128
00:10:22,669 --> 00:10:23,790
It's a peace envoy?

129
00:10:25,121 --> 00:10:28,564
They're probably adventurers who
don't understand what's going on here.

130
00:10:30,026 --> 00:10:31,887
Certainly, if that's your story.

131
00:10:34,930 --> 00:10:39,214
But in these cold, calculating
eyes, I see bloodlust.

132
00:10:40,916 --> 00:10:42,517
I know how the town folk feel.

133
00:10:42,857 --> 00:10:46,301
They tremble at the sight
of me, loathe my existence.

134
00:10:46,661 --> 00:10:49,363
But despite that, they
still view me as a person.

135
00:10:50,615 --> 00:10:51,155
Not you.

136
00:10:51,816 --> 00:10:56,298
Whenever you look at my face, you see
only a wild beast that should be put down.

137
00:10:56,898 --> 00:10:58,379
And is that not what you are?

138
00:10:59,059 --> 00:11:01,780
Demons are simply monsters
who have learned human speech.

139
00:11:02,801 --> 00:11:04,482
You only communicate with lies.

140
00:11:06,783 --> 00:11:08,403
Throw her in the
mansion's dungeon.

141
00:11:09,104 --> 00:11:09,564
My lord!

142
00:11:10,424 --> 00:11:18,068
Hey, wait!

143
00:11:32,648 --> 00:11:33,969
This is so boring.

144
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:40,242
We have bad news.

145
00:11:41,132 --> 00:11:43,193
They say you'll be down
here for two or three years.

146
00:11:43,733 --> 00:11:45,354
A shorter term than I expected.

147
00:11:46,495 --> 00:11:48,316
Could you bring me
a few grimoires later?

148
00:11:49,816 --> 00:11:53,758
I know you don't experience time as
humans do, but this is going a bit too far.

149
00:11:54,318 --> 00:11:56,940
It's not as though I actively
chose to be locked away.

150
00:11:58,297 --> 00:12:02,079
So, what did he mean when he
called those demons Peace Envoys?

151
00:12:02,879 --> 00:12:04,920
I tried to get some
information while shopping.

152
00:12:05,881 --> 00:12:06,901
Aura the guillotine.

153
00:12:07,101 --> 00:12:08,302
You have heard of her, right?

154
00:12:08,742 --> 00:12:10,523
The Seven Sages of Destruction.

155
00:12:11,163 --> 00:12:12,444
And Aura was one of them.

156
00:12:13,865 --> 00:12:15,465
She was a servant
of the Demon King.

157
00:12:15,745 --> 00:12:19,087
We killed most of her followers, but
she slipped away and disappeared.

158
00:12:19,928 --> 00:12:20,848
Has she re-emerged?

159
00:12:21,872 --> 00:12:22,572
Afraid so.

160
00:12:22,993 --> 00:12:25,674
I'm told that she came
back to power 28 years ago.

161
00:12:26,674 --> 00:12:29,535
Since then, her forces have
been locked in battle with this town.

162
00:12:29,795 --> 00:12:31,396
There have been many casualties.

163
00:12:32,096 --> 00:12:34,758
But the demons have grown
exhausted by the endless fighting.

164
00:12:35,378 --> 00:12:37,139
They've come here
to propose a truce.

165
00:12:37,999 --> 00:12:40,260
Which is why they were
let inside as envoys.

166
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:41,941
How unwise.

167
00:12:42,761 --> 00:12:45,142
There's no use trying to
negotiate with their kind.

168
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,201
Surely some good can come of it.

169
00:12:48,522 --> 00:12:49,502
Why not speak to them?

170
00:12:49,923 --> 00:12:53,365
Wouldn't the best option be to stop fighting
and start talking their problems out?

171
00:12:53,866 --> 00:12:54,126
No.

172
00:12:54,646 --> 00:12:56,267
Nothing will be
resolved that way.

173
00:12:58,389 --> 00:13:00,571
Demons are beasts
who seek to devour.

174
00:13:01,231 --> 00:13:05,614
Have you ever wondered why those monsters
chose to speak the same language as humans?

175
00:13:10,558 --> 00:13:11,158
Please, Hero.

176
00:13:11,839 --> 00:13:13,040
You must slay this devil.

177
00:13:18,322 --> 00:13:19,382
It's only a child.

178
00:13:20,043 --> 00:13:20,343
No!

179
00:13:20,563 --> 00:13:22,104
Don't be fooled
by its appearance!

180
00:13:22,544 --> 00:13:23,184
It ate her!

181
00:13:23,384 --> 00:13:24,624
My daughter is dead!

182
00:13:24,745 --> 00:13:25,665
Swing your sword!

183
00:13:31,867 --> 00:13:32,588
It hurts.

184
00:13:35,609 --> 00:13:36,489
Make it stop.

185
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:39,190
Please, Mommy.

186
00:13:46,382 --> 00:13:46,963
Step away.

187
00:13:47,603 --> 00:13:48,404
I'll handle this.

188
00:13:49,485 --> 00:13:52,447
Kill her, and we'd be
no better than them.

189
00:13:54,929 --> 00:13:59,393
My friends, surely this scared little girl
can eat what we do in order to survive.

190
00:14:00,133 --> 00:14:03,196
Why don't we give her the
opportunity to atone for her mistakes?

191
00:14:04,016 --> 00:14:05,077
No, Chief, you can't!

192
00:14:05,417 --> 00:14:06,358
Are you crazy?!

193
00:14:06,378 --> 00:14:08,360
It took our daughter!

194
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:12,443
I'll never hold her again!

195
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,520
Here, let me tend
to your wounds.

196
00:14:18,881 --> 00:14:19,441
You're in luck.

197
00:14:20,181 --> 00:14:22,682
I've been looking for somebody
to help out around the farm.

198
00:14:25,242 --> 00:14:29,863
Himmel, you're going to regret
not killing this girl, this demon.

199
00:14:30,623 --> 00:14:31,124
She's here.

200
00:14:31,884 --> 00:14:33,484
Why don't you
speak to her and see?

201
00:14:34,684 --> 00:14:36,705
We'll be in this village
for some time anyway.

202
00:14:37,125 --> 00:14:38,025
We might as well try.

203
00:14:41,606 --> 00:14:41,906
Fine.

204
00:15:16,498 --> 00:15:18,218
Why did you murder
the village chief?

205
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:25,800
We should have
killed it at once!

206
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:28,121
These monsters
cannot live among us!

207
00:15:29,061 --> 00:15:29,981
There it is again.

208
00:15:30,001 --> 00:15:36,943
Every day since I came here,
I've felt your desire to kill me.

209
00:15:37,903 --> 00:15:39,704
But I just wanted
to live in harmony.

210
00:15:41,145 --> 00:15:43,108
I figured out a way
to make things right.

211
00:15:43,849 --> 00:15:47,353
Here, take this child as a
replacement for your offspring.

212
00:15:47,374 --> 00:15:48,876
The one I ate.

213
00:15:50,618 --> 00:15:52,781
That girl is the daughter
of the village chief.

214
00:15:53,762 --> 00:15:55,765
Yes, but he isn't alive anymore.

215
00:16:02,604 --> 00:16:07,406
Despite my good intentions, it seems as though
I've unfortunately made another mistake.

216
00:16:07,726 --> 00:16:09,247
You've given me no choice.

217
00:16:09,267 --> 00:16:11,408
I'm taking this child hostage.

218
00:16:18,771 --> 00:16:19,892
You won't stop me again?

219
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:22,060
No.

220
00:16:23,533 --> 00:16:24,474
Mommy, please.

221
00:16:31,399 --> 00:16:32,940
Why call out to a mother?

222
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:37,742
Demons are monsters, and like all
monsters, they don't raise their young.

223
00:16:38,302 --> 00:16:39,903
Once born, you are abandoned.

224
00:16:40,403 --> 00:16:42,064
You walk this world alone.

225
00:16:43,344 --> 00:16:45,946
That makes you
ruthless, solitary creatures.

226
00:16:46,526 --> 00:16:49,547
Lone wolves with no
concept of what family means.

227
00:16:50,708 --> 00:16:51,228
Explain.

228
00:16:51,948 --> 00:16:54,329
Why would you call out to a
mother you've never known?

229
00:16:56,410 --> 00:16:57,131
It's simple.

230
00:16:58,231 --> 00:16:59,572
That word stops humans.

231
00:17:00,981 --> 00:17:02,682
It keeps them from murdering us.

232
00:17:03,283 --> 00:17:04,404
Isn't that magical?

233
00:17:08,227 --> 00:17:10,208
Demons use words
to trick humans.

234
00:17:10,589 --> 00:17:12,190
You can't trust
a thing they say.

235
00:17:13,411 --> 00:17:15,172
They're monsters
who learn to speak.

236
00:17:15,573 --> 00:17:18,155
That's how the legendary
mage Flamme defined them.

237
00:17:19,115 --> 00:17:20,116
It's in their blood.

238
00:17:20,376 --> 00:17:22,058
They're descended from liars.

239
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:26,181
Monsters who found they could
lure in humans by crying, help me.

240
00:17:32,055 --> 00:17:33,716
Don't forget about
the grimoires.

241
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:40,261
Granat is late.

242
00:17:41,022 --> 00:17:41,742
What insolence.

243
00:17:42,503 --> 00:17:44,364
It's a human diplomatic tactic.

244
00:17:45,705 --> 00:17:49,108
Frankly, I'm more curious
about the rogue mage.

245
00:17:50,509 --> 00:17:52,070
I've seen her face before.

246
00:17:54,992 --> 00:17:57,474
Wild beasts who only
communicate with lies.

247
00:17:58,643 --> 00:18:00,544
It's not an inaccurate
description.

248
00:18:01,665 --> 00:18:03,366
She can see us for what we are.

249
00:18:03,667 --> 00:18:06,409
No one else in this town
understands our true nature.

250
00:18:07,729 --> 00:18:09,231
Or perhaps she's just logical.

251
00:18:09,611 --> 00:18:12,813
She knows there's but one
reason to learn our prey's language.

252
00:18:13,954 --> 00:18:16,195
They talk to us so that
they may deceive us.

253
00:18:16,796 --> 00:18:18,497
Every word is a baited trap.

254
00:18:19,778 --> 00:18:21,940
This town won't be
standing for much longer.

255
00:18:22,840 --> 00:18:25,342
I should use the confusion
as a cover to escape.

256
00:18:33,335 --> 00:18:33,955
Where are we?

257
00:18:35,957 --> 00:18:37,398
This is my son's room.

258
00:18:41,601 --> 00:18:42,662
He was a good boy.

259
00:18:43,983 --> 00:18:49,647
He'd often boast that he'd take control of the
family soon, offering me a chance to finally relax.

260
00:18:57,272 --> 00:19:01,155
He fought bravely alongside His
Majesty, who then gifted him this sword.

261
00:19:01,789 --> 00:19:03,570
And where might your son be now?

262
00:19:07,973 --> 00:19:11,195
He died in battle against your
leader, Aura, ten years ago.

263
00:19:19,419 --> 00:19:21,841
This sword is all
that was left of him.

264
00:19:22,401 --> 00:19:23,662
You monster!

265
00:19:26,439 --> 00:19:30,362
I invited you here to avenge my
boy, the child you took from me.

266
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:32,484
I will slaughter
you in his name.

267
00:19:33,525 --> 00:19:35,387
Your peace means nothing to me!

268
00:19:46,796 --> 00:19:49,658
Allow me to compliment the
tidiness of your son's room.

269
00:19:50,999 --> 00:19:53,682
I wager you've kept it just
as it was ten years ago.

270
00:19:55,027 --> 00:19:56,408
What does it matter to you?

271
00:19:57,208 --> 00:20:02,331
I've kept my father's room the same since he was
lost to us two, from when you struck him down.

272
00:20:04,953 --> 00:20:07,774
We can put an end to
all of this, don't you see?

273
00:20:08,955 --> 00:20:14,458
Or we can go on spilling each other's blood,
causing more grief, ruining more lives.

274
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:19,521
We can speak to one
another, can we not?

275
00:20:20,022 --> 00:20:22,263
So please, let's
find another way.

276
00:20:34,075 --> 00:20:35,416
Show them to the guest room.

277
00:20:42,142 --> 00:20:43,243
I shall consider this.

278
00:20:52,972 --> 00:20:55,834
Lord Lügner, what is a father?

279
00:20:57,335 --> 00:20:57,976
Who can say?

280
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:13,623
Graf Granat resents us, but he is also an empathetic
man, and that's a flaw we can wield against him.

281
00:21:15,563 --> 00:21:21,706
I aim to win his trust, and if I do, I'll ask him to lower
the town's defensive barrier as a show of good faith.

282
00:21:22,626 --> 00:21:26,868
Then Lady Aura's forces will raze
this meddlesome town and feast.

283
00:21:30,930 --> 00:21:33,351
I can't help but notice
it's just you and me, Linie.

284
00:21:34,191 --> 00:21:35,472
Where has Draht run off to?

285
00:21:35,976 --> 00:21:38,098
He said he was
eliminating an obstacle.

286
00:21:39,379 --> 00:21:40,640
How irresponsible.

287
00:21:41,621 --> 00:21:43,562
What will I do with
that reckless youth?

288
00:21:48,006 --> 00:21:48,607
Lord Draht!

289
00:21:49,287 --> 00:21:50,768
This area is
forbidden to guests.

290
00:21:51,229 --> 00:21:51,969
Why are you here?

291
00:21:52,690 --> 00:21:53,691
Please, return to-

292
00:22:05,966 --> 00:22:08,668
Sorry, I'm told
visiting hours are over.

293
00:22:11,610 --> 00:22:13,652
I'm an executioner named Draht.

294
00:22:14,012 --> 00:22:15,473
I serve Aura, the guillotine.

295
00:22:15,733 --> 00:22:16,374
Don't fight.

296
00:22:17,154 --> 00:22:18,535
I have come here to kill you.

297
00:22:20,136 --> 00:22:20,617
I see.

298
00:22:21,337 --> 00:22:23,059
Not pretending you
want peace anymore?

299
00:22:24,199 --> 00:22:24,960
We've just begun.

300
00:22:27,647 --> 00:22:32,108
According to Lord Lügner, this girl is
the only obstacle standing in our way.

301
00:22:32,969 --> 00:22:38,771
If I dispose of her now, and we get Graf
Granat to trust us, this town will crumble.

302
00:22:40,571 --> 00:22:42,772
I should warn you
that I am fairly strong.

303
00:22:44,773 --> 00:22:45,573
Stronger than me?

304
00:22:47,113 --> 00:22:49,214
Stronger even than
Aura the guillotine.

